────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  2.5  CITIZEN REGISTRATION FLOW  (by Village Officer)
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

  [Village Officer App — inside village geo-fence]
          │
          ▼
  STEP 1: Enter National ID Number
          │  • System checks citizen age ≥ 18 (from NIDA DOB)
          │  • Rejects if under 18
          ▼
  STEP 2: NIDA API Fetch
          │  • Auto-populate: name, DOB, gender, parent IDs
          │  • Check disability flag in NIDA record
          │    - If disability flag = YES → ask officer:
          │      "Still disabled?" or "Cured?"
          │      (allow selecting cured disabilities for multi-disabled)
          ▼
  STEP 3: Biometric Capture
          │  • Take live photo (camera)
          │  • Capture fingerprints (hardware scanner)
          │  • Capture signature (touchscreen)
          ▼
  STEP 4: Extended Personal Details
          │  • Disability type(s): Hearing / Sight / etc. (multi-select)
          │  • Disability cause: Road accident / Born with / etc.
          │  • Education level (select one):
          │    None / Primary / O-Level / A-Level / Certificate /
          │    Diploma / Bachelor's / Master's / PhD / Other
          │  • Village street name
          │  • House registration number
          │  • Marital status (Yes/No)
          │    - If Yes → recommend marriage registration (optional, with consent)
          │  • Children National IDs (add multiple)
          │  • Occupation (primary + additional economic activities)
          ▼
  STEP 5: Optional / Supplementary Details
          │  • Land ownership in acres (optional)
          │  • Animal keeping category (multi-select):
          │    Livestock (cows/goats/pigs) / Birds (hens) / Other (dogs/donkeys)
          │  • Health insurance provider(s) (multi-select)
          │  • Communication devices (multi-select):
          │    Mobile (kitochi / smartphone) / Computer / Radio / Television
          │  • Social Mutual Fund memberships (multi-select):
          │    NSSF / TASAF / etc.
          ▼
  STEP 6: Review & Confirm
          │  • Officer reviews all captured data
          │  • Citizen confirms (verbal or signature)
          ▼
  STEP 7: National ID Card Issued
          │  • System assigns unique National ID (if new birth registration)
          │  • Citizen status set to: ALIVE
          │  • ID card print payload generated
          │  • Card expiry = date of issue + 10 years
          │  • After 10 years: citizen must return to update photo,
          │    fingerprints, and signature for renewal
          ▼
  [Citizen Record Created in Database]


────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  2.6  BIRTH REGISTRATION FLOW  (by Hospital Officer)
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

  [Hospital Officer App — inside facility geo-fence]
          │
          ▼
  STEP 1: Enter Birth Details
          │  • Child first name, middle name, surname
          │  • Gender (Male / Female)
          │  • Date of birth
          ▼
  STEP 2: Link Parents
          │  • Father National ID → validate in system
          │  • Mother National ID → validate in system
          │  • System links child to parent lineage records
          ▼
  STEP 3: Link Facility & Officer
          │  • Facility ID auto-attached (from officer profile)
          │  • Officer (doctor/nurse) National ID linked
          ▼
  STEP 4: Generate National ID for Child
          │  • System auto-generates unique National ID for newborn
          │  • Child status set to: ALIVE
          │  • Age tracking starts from DOB
          │    (auto-increments every year while status = ALIVE)
          ▼
  STEP 5: Issue Birth Certificate
          │  • PDF certificate generated
          │  • QR code embedded (digitally signed)
          │  • Pushed to RITA API for civil registry sync
          ▼
  NOTE: When child turns 18 → must visit Village Officer
        to register full citizen profile and receive National ID card


────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  2.7  DEATH REGISTRATION FLOW
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

  CASE A — Death OUTSIDE hospital (Village Officer registers):
          │
          ▼
  • Enter citizen National ID
  • System fetches citizen info
  • Enter: date of death, cause/reason of death
  • Citizen status updated to: DECEASED
  • Age counter frozen at last recorded age
  • Death certificate generated (PDF + QR)
  • Pushed to RITA


  CASE B — Death INSIDE hospital (Hospital Officer registers):
          │
          ▼
  • Select category: INFANT or ADULT
  │
  ├─► If INFANT:
  │     • Enter father National ID
  │     • Enter mother National ID
  │     • Date of death
  │     • Cause/reason (if applicable)
  │     • Certificate generated → pushed to RITA
  │
  └─► If ADULT:
        • Enter citizen National ID → fetch all info
        • Enter cause of death
        • Enter date of death
        • Link duty officer (doctor/nurse) National ID
        • Citizen status → DECEASED
        • Certificate generated → pushed to RITA


────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  2.8  MARRIAGE REGISTRATION FLOW  (by Village Officer)
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

  STEP 1: Enter National IDs
          │  • Husband National ID → fetch & verify citizen record
          │  • Wife National ID → fetch & verify citizen record
          ▼
  STEP 2: Validate Marriage Rules
          │  MALE:   Can have multiple wives simultaneously
          │  FEMALE: Can have only ONE husband at a time.
          │          Exception: allowed to register new marriage if
          │          last husband's vital_status = DECEASED
          │          or last marriage status = UNREGISTERED
          ▼
  STEP 3: Generate Marriage Certificate
          │  • System assigns unique marriage_id
          │  • Certificate PDF generated (template TBD)
          │  • Marriage status set to: ACTIVE
          │  • Pushed to RITA
          ▼
  [Marriage Record Created — used for lineage tracking]


  UNREGISTER MARRIAGE FLOW:
  ──────────────────────────
  • Officer enters marriage_id
  • Submits unregister request
  • Request sent to authorized institution for verification
  • Institution provides vivid reason for dissolution
  • On approval:
    - Marriage status → DISSOLVED or UNREGISTERED
    - dissolution_date, dissolution_reason, dissolution_authority recorded
  • Wife's marital lock released → eligible to re-marry


────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  2.9  MIGRATION REGISTRATION FLOW  (by Village Officer)
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

  [Source Village Officer — citizen's current village]
          │
          ▼
  STEP 1: Officer enters citizen National ID
          │  • System returns current residence info
          ▼
  STEP 2: Enter Migration Details
          │  • New residence: Region → District → Ward → Village
          │  • Reason for migration:
          │    Economic activities / Job / Family / Education / Other
          ▼
  STEP 3: Migration Request Created
          │  • Status: PENDING
          │  • Expiry: request_date + 30 days
          │  • Notification sent to TARGET village officer
          ▼
  [Citizen must physically visit target village within 30 days]
          │
          ▼
  STEP 4: Target Village Officer Receives Request
          │  • Sees pending migration request in app
          │  • Verifies citizen identity in person
          ▼
  STEP 5: Confirm or Reject
          │
          ├─► CONFIRMED:
          │     • Citizen residential info updated to new village
          │     • Migration status → CONFIRMED
          │     • Population counts auto-updated in both villages
          │
          ├─► REJECTED:
          │     • Migration status → CANCELLED
          │     • Reason recorded
          │
          └─► NO ACTION within 30 days:
                • System auto-cancels request
                • Migration status → EXPIRED
                • Citizen remains at original village




