  SECTION 4 — SECURITY & PRIVACY ARCHITECTURE
████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████


════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
  4.1  AUTHENTICATION SECURITY
════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

  PASSWORD HASHING
  • Algorithm: bcrypt with cost factor ≥ 12
  • Never stored in plaintext at any point

  JSON WEB TOKENS (JWT)
  • Access token TTL:  15 minutes
  • Refresh token TTL: 7 days (rotated on each use)
  • Signed with RS256 (asymmetric key pair)
  • Stored in HttpOnly cookies (web) / secure storage (mobile)

  ONE-TIME LOGIN TOKENS
  • Generated as signed JWT (separate signing key)
  • SHA-256 hash stored in DB (never the raw token)
  • TTL: 24 hours
  • Single-use: invalidated immediately after first successful use
  • Cannot be reused or extended

  MULTI-FACTOR AUTHENTICATION (MFA)
  • Method 1: TOTP (RFC 6238) via authenticator app (optional)
  • Method 2: SMS OTP — 6-digit code, 5-minute TTL
  • Backup codes: 8 single-use codes generated at MFA setup

  ACCOUNT PROTECTION
  • Lockout after 5 consecutive failed login attempts
  • Exponential backoff: 1m → 5m → 15m → 1h → permanent lock
  • Permanent lock requires admin reset
  • Session invalidated on: password change, device change, admin suspension


════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
  4.2  DEVICE BINDING & GEO-FENCE SECURITY
════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

  DEVICE FINGERPRINT GENERATION
  • Formula: HMAC-SHA256 ( device_id + OS_version + hardware_hash )
  • Captured silently during initial token activation
  • Stored as hashed value in village_officers / hospital_officers table
  • One device per officer — cannot be changed without district admin reset

  GEO-FENCE ENFORCEMENT
  • Village boundaries stored as PostGIS GEOGRAPHY(Polygon) in DB
  • On every app session start:
      GPS coordinate captured → ST_Within(officer_gps, geo_fence_polygon)
      If FALSE → session blocked, error shown
  • Offline mode: geo-fence polygon cached locally (encrypted)
  • Sync happens automatically when connection restored

  BLOCKING CONDITIONS
  • Device ID doesn't match bound device → BLOCKED
  • GPS outside assigned boundary → BLOCKED
  • Token expired before device binding completes → RESTART required
  • App detects mock/spoofed GPS (via sensor fusion checks) → BLOCKED


════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
  4.3  DATA ENCRYPTION
════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

  IN TRANSIT
  • All HTTP traffic: TLS 1.3 (minimum TLS 1.2)
  • Service-to-service: Mutual TLS (mTLS)
  • Mobile apps: certificate pinning

  AT REST
  • PostgreSQL tablespace: AES-256 encryption
  • Column-level (pgcrypto): NIDA numbers, biometric templates, MFA secrets
  • Fingerprint templates: AES-256-GCM encrypted BEFORE storing
  • Object storage (photos, PDFs): Server-Side Encryption (SSE-S3 or SSE-KMS)

  KEY MANAGEMENT
  • Master keys: Hardware Security Module (HSM) or cloud KMS
  • Separate encryption keys per data classification:
      - PUBLIC: unencrypted aggregated stats
      - INTERNAL: user metadata
      - CONFIDENTIAL: citizen PII
      - RESTRICTED: biometric data, NIDA numbers
  • Automatic key rotation: every 90 days
  • Encrypted backups with separate backup key


════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
  4.4  ROLE-BASED ACCESS CONTROL (RBAC)
════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

  ROLE               READ                          WRITE
  ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  Super Admin        ALL tables, ALL regions        All (incl. user mgmt)
  District Admin     Own district only              Officer CRUD in district
  Village Officer    Own village citizens only      Citizen, building, infra,
                                                    marriage, migration, death
  Hospital Officer   Own facility records only      Birth, death (facility)
  Public User        Aggregated/anonymized only     None (read-only)
  ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

  • Row-Level Security (RLS) enforced at PostgreSQL database level
  • API middleware validates scope before every query
  • Public citizen app receives ZERO personally identifiable information
  • Researcher data access requires NBS authorization + consent framework


════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
  4.5  AUDIT TRAIL
════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

  • Every INSERT, UPDATE, DELETE triggers audit_log entry
  • Logs are APPEND-ONLY (no UPDATE or DELETE on audit_logs allowed)
  • Each log entry captures:
      - Who acted (actor_id, actor_role)
      - What they did (action, target_table, target_id)
      - What changed (old_data JSONB, new_data JSONB)
      - Where from (ip_address, gps_coordinates for mobile officers)
      - When (timestamp)
  • Super Admin can search/filter all logs
  • Automated alerts on:
      - Unusual data access volumes
      - Access from unexpected IP/location
      - Multiple failed login attempts
      - Off-hours officer activity


════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
  4.6  NETWORK SECURITY
════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

  • Super/District Admin dashboards: VPN or IP whitelist required
  • API rate limiting: per-user and per-endpoint via Redis
  • CORS: restricted to known app origins only
  • DDoS protection: CDN/WAF layer (CloudFront + WAF or equivalent)
  • API Gateway: request schema validation, payload size limits
  • NIDA & external APIs: whitelisted egress IPs only
  • Intrusion detection system (IDS) on all network segments


════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
  4.7  PRIVACY BY DESIGN
════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

  • Public app shows ZERO PII — only aggregate population statistics
  • Biometric data physically separated from PII in storage
  • Data minimization: optional fields collected only with citizen consent
  • Research/external access: authorized via NBS consent framework only
  • Data classification enforced at all layers
  • Certificate QR codes contain digitally signed payload (government PKI)
  • Right to anonymization for withdrawn research consent




